;W[rp]LB[qs:1][oq:2][ss:3][or:4][sq:5][rp:6]C[Dia.3 Both sides make mistakes

In this diagram, Black has messed up just as bad as White has.  When Black plays 1, White will take the vital point at 2.  Here's where it gets tricky.  Black will take at 3 but since White knows Black is low on liberties he can play at 4.  Black can take a stone but that only gives him one eye, and as you can see, Black is dead once we reach 6.
